<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
When parsing a form like "key&" (a key with no value) the state machine reaches PP_Callback with start_value == NULL and end_value == NULL. The code then calls process_value(pp, start_value, end_value, NULL) i.e. process_value(pp, NULL, NULL, NULL). If process_value uses any <string.h> functions (for example strlen, memcpy, strcpy, etc.) on the passed pointers, those functions would be invoked with invalid (NULL) or out-of-range pointers and could access beyond the bounds of the referenced objects, violating MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17.
</scenario>

